The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 September is 295,569 (34,066.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 September, there were 419 new confirmed cases (48.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 August, there were 394 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 6% (25 extra cases).
